text.section:
When a unit uses competitive sealed bidding to award a procurement contract, the unit may give a preference to the resident bidder who submits the lowest responsive bid from a resident bidder if:
the resident bidder is a responsible bidder;
a responsible bidder whose principal office or operation is in another state submits the lowest responsive bid;
the state in which the nonresident bidder's principal office is located or the state in which the nonresident bidder has its principal operation through which it would provide supplies or services gives a preference to its residents; and
a preference does not conflict with a federal law or grant affecting the procurement contract.
